1
00:01:50,020 --> 00:01:56,100
=Later, I Laughed=

2
00:01:56,180 --> 00:01:58,180
=Episode 24=

3
00:01:59,180 --> 00:02:01,940
(No.9 Traditional Chinese
and Western Medicine Hospital)

4
00:02:19,660 --> 00:02:21,340
I don't have lung cancer.

5
00:02:28,340 --> 00:02:30,260
Now you smoke openly without a care.

6
00:02:30,580 --> 00:02:32,300
The surgery is in three days.

7
00:02:33,180 --> 00:02:34,300
Let's still be careful.

8
00:02:36,300 --> 00:02:38,260
Xiuya's going to
the stand-up comedy competition?

9
00:02:41,100 --> 00:02:43,900
What's the competition like?

10
00:02:45,220 --> 00:02:46,180
I don't know.

11
00:02:47,620 --> 00:02:51,180
What is it about stand-up comedy

12
00:02:51,580 --> 00:02:53,300
that makes Xiuya go all out for it?

13
00:02:55,980 --> 00:02:57,940
I want to go see the competition.

14
00:03:00,140 --> 00:03:02,020
Let's not mess around
before the surgery.

15
00:03:03,260 --> 00:03:04,260
Go rest.

16
00:03:04,460 --> 00:03:06,300
Even the doctor can't guarantee it.

17
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:08,060
What if I can't get off
the operating table?

18
00:03:10,100 --> 00:03:11,100
Don't say that.

19
00:03:11,620 --> 00:03:12,460
It'll be fine.

20
00:03:14,660 --> 00:03:16,020
Heaven rewards the good.

21
00:03:17,140 --> 00:03:18,500
I really want to see

22
00:03:19,020 --> 00:03:21,660
what my daughter's like on stage.

23
00:03:22,860 --> 00:03:25,300
So, this treatment involves
tapping your acupressure points

24
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:26,780
to help you lose weight quickly.

25
00:03:27,180 --> 00:03:28,540
I got hit all over.

26
00:03:30,300 --> 00:03:31,300
And they kept promising

27
00:03:31,300 --> 00:03:33,780
to make all customers satisfied.

28
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:34,760
- 100% satisfaction.
- Sorry.

29
00:03:34,760 --> 00:03:36,530
- Excuse me.
- Of course you'll be satisfied.

30
00:03:36,530 --> 00:03:37,540
Who wouldn't be?

31
00:03:39,020 --> 00:03:41,540
If you're not satisfied, you'll get
another round of treatment

32
00:03:42,820 --> 00:03:44,180
until you are!

33
00:03:44,780 --> 00:03:46,300
Are you satisfied now?

34
00:03:46,900 --> 00:03:47,940
You must be.

35
00:03:49,180 --> 00:03:50,660
Isn't it obvious you've lost weight?

36
00:03:51,160 --> 00:03:52,860
Don't you want to share it
on social media?

37
00:03:54,660 --> 00:03:55,940
Thanks, everyone! I'm Rock.

38
00:03:59,270 --> 00:04:00,180
Thank you

39
00:04:00,180 --> 00:04:03,780
for the wonderful performance.

40
00:04:04,260 --> 00:04:05,100
Now, friends,

41
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:07,380
do you want to vote for Rock?

42
00:04:07,660 --> 00:04:08,500
Yeah!

43
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:10,080
Do you want to cheer for him?

44
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,430
Do you want him to be the champion?

45
00:04:11,540 --> 00:04:12,380
Yeah!

46
00:04:12,580 --> 00:04:14,660
If you liked
this performer's performance,

47
00:04:14,660 --> 00:04:16,060
please use your voting device

48
00:04:16,060 --> 00:04:17,380
to cast your vote for him.

49
00:04:21,260 --> 00:04:24,260
Three, two, one, vote locked!

50
00:04:24,660 --> 00:04:25,660
Voting time is over.

51
00:04:25,660 --> 00:04:27,780
Next up, we have a contestant

52
00:04:28,380 --> 00:04:30,100
who used to work at a big company

53
00:04:30,220 --> 00:04:32,460
as a white-collar worker.

54
00:04:32,620 --> 00:04:34,780
She now works full-time

55
00:04:34,780 --> 00:04:35,940
as a stand-up comedian.

56
00:04:36,140 --> 00:04:37,860
She has vividly shown us

57
00:04:37,860 --> 00:04:39,700
through her actions

58
00:04:39,700 --> 00:04:43,140
what it's like when life starts to feel
like the walls are closing in.

59
00:04:44,260 --> 00:04:46,020
I really want to talk to her
and understand

60
00:04:46,260 --> 00:04:48,020
why she made such a decision.

61
00:04:48,020 --> 00:04:50,300
Let's welcome Wu Xiuya!

62
00:04:50,300 --> 00:04:52,720
Okay!

63
00:05:00,860 --> 00:05:02,700
Hello everyone! My name is Wu Xiuya.

64
00:05:11,420 --> 00:05:13,860
Right now, I'm a full-time
stand-up comedian.

65
00:05:14,180 --> 00:05:16,300
Stand-up comedy has given me
so many things:

66
00:05:16,580 --> 00:05:19,700
my old job, my old colleagues,
and my ex-boyfriend.

67
00:05:20,740 --> 00:05:23,180
In other words, I have nothing left now.

68
00:05:25,020 --> 00:05:26,460
A lot of people are curious about

69
00:05:26,460 --> 00:05:28,860
why I quit a stable job

70
00:05:28,860 --> 00:05:30,300
to do stand-up comedy.

71
00:05:30,700 --> 00:05:32,260
Well, think about it.

72
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:34,300
If I could do stand-up comedy,

73
00:05:34,300 --> 00:05:36,300
there's no way
my job would be that great.

74
00:05:37,700 --> 00:05:38,700
Let me put it this way,

75
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:40,540
if my job were going well,

76
00:05:40,540 --> 00:05:42,020
I wouldn't be doing this.

77
00:05:43,540 --> 00:05:45,050
The good thing about stand-up comedy is

78
00:05:45,050 --> 00:05:47,140
to let me meet so many new people.

79
00:05:47,300 --> 00:05:49,300
Since joining the stand-up comedy world,

80
00:05:49,300 --> 00:05:51,860
I've met all sorts of people

81
00:05:51,860 --> 00:05:54,300
who are failures from all walks of life.

82
00:05:55,740 --> 00:05:58,580
There's a guy in his forties
who lost money running a bar,

83
00:05:58,740 --> 00:06:01,860
a guy in his thirties
living in a caravan

84
00:06:02,020 --> 00:06:03,580
and says, "I drive my caravan,

85
00:06:03,580 --> 00:06:04,860
I sleep wherever I want,

86
00:06:04,860 --> 00:06:06,020
that's freedom."

87
00:06:07,060 --> 00:06:09,100
Then a security guard
knocks on the window and says,

88
00:06:09,100 --> 00:06:09,980
"You can't park here."

89
00:06:10,020 --> 00:06:11,340
"Sorry, sir,

90
00:06:11,340 --> 00:06:12,420
I'm leaving now."

91
00:06:12,700 --> 00:06:14,900
He says he's free and untethered,

92
00:06:14,980 --> 00:06:17,220
but when a parking lot charges him,
he leaves right away.

93
00:06:18,740 --> 00:06:20,540
And there's a guy in his twenties

94
00:06:20,540 --> 00:06:21,980
studying aquaculture in college.

95
00:06:22,900 --> 00:06:24,700
Just listen to that major,

96
00:06:24,700 --> 00:06:26,100
aquaculture.

97
00:06:26,180 --> 00:06:27,540
You can tell right away

98
00:06:27,540 --> 00:06:29,860
he's already lost at the starting line.

99
00:06:30,100 --> 00:06:31,740
I didn't even know

100
00:06:31,980 --> 00:06:34,300
people could study
aquaculture in college.

101
00:06:34,420 --> 00:06:36,420
I thought it was something
you learned at sea.

102
00:06:38,420 --> 00:06:39,340
I didn't start out

103
00:06:39,340 --> 00:06:41,420
like these stand-up comedian guys.

104
00:06:41,540 --> 00:06:42,980
I used to have a serious job.

105
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:46,020
I worked in the Corporate Communication
Department of a big company.

106
00:06:46,220 --> 00:06:48,900
Our job was pretty simple.

107
00:06:48,980 --> 00:06:51,860
First, write speeches for the boss.

108
00:06:51,860 --> 00:06:52,700
Second,

109
00:06:52,700 --> 00:06:54,480
type up the speeches

110
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:56,300
and post them
on the company's public account.

111
00:06:57,420 --> 00:06:58,780
Basically,

112
00:06:58,780 --> 00:07:01,700
I was the bridge between the boss

113
00:07:01,700 --> 00:07:03,180
and the employees.

114
00:07:04,540 --> 00:07:06,420
Now you know how important I was.

115
00:07:06,980 --> 00:07:08,860
- Sometimes I'd wonder,
- Have some water.

116
00:07:08,860 --> 00:07:09,900
if I just posted

117
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:13,340
the boss's speeches without him,

118
00:07:13,540 --> 00:07:15,780
would the company still need him?

119
00:07:17,780 --> 00:07:20,220
Everyone trusted me at work.

120
00:07:20,220 --> 00:07:21,700
They'd give me

121
00:07:21,700 --> 00:07:22,900
all the important tasks

122
00:07:22,980 --> 00:07:25,780
and then go have some hot pot.

123
00:07:27,980 --> 00:07:29,780
My co-workers

124
00:07:29,780 --> 00:07:31,700
were kind enough to comfort me,

125
00:07:32,300 --> 00:07:33,140
"Xiuya,

126
00:07:33,540 --> 00:07:36,340
I only trust you with the work.

127
00:07:36,550 --> 00:07:38,740
I only hang out with the others
for fun."

128
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:41,740
Being good at work

129
00:07:41,740 --> 00:07:44,780
is the modern version
of a woman's chastity belt.

130
00:07:44,780 --> 00:07:46,150
Once you get tagged as "competent",

131
00:07:46,150 --> 00:07:47,740
you can never take it off.

132
00:07:47,980 --> 00:07:50,420
But I didn't just want to be trusted,

133
00:07:50,900 --> 00:07:52,980
I wanted to have fun too.

134
00:07:55,220 --> 00:07:56,540
My friend told me

135
00:07:56,540 --> 00:07:58,340
I have a people-pleasing personality.

136
00:07:58,540 --> 00:07:59,700
I said, "I don't!"

137
00:08:00,100 --> 00:08:01,780
She said, "How can you say you don't?"

138
00:08:02,700 --> 00:08:03,540
I said, "I do."

139
00:08:06,100 --> 00:08:07,220
She didn't know that

140
00:08:07,220 --> 00:08:09,420
I really wasn't a people-pleaser,

141
00:08:09,900 --> 00:08:12,900
I just didn't want her to be angry.

142
00:08:15,490 --> 00:08:16,340
Later,

143
00:08:16,340 --> 00:08:18,420
I tried stand-up comedy
for the first time

144
00:08:18,860 --> 00:08:20,980
and said a lot of things
I would never say normally.

145
00:08:20,980 --> 00:08:22,700
I realized that on stage,

146
00:08:22,700 --> 00:08:23,980
I was finally being my true self.

147
00:08:24,860 --> 00:08:26,800
Although stand-up comedy
doesn't make much money,

148
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:28,900
it lets me listen to my own voice

149
00:08:28,900 --> 00:08:30,180
instead of others'.

150
00:08:30,180 --> 00:08:31,300
I can do whatever I want.

151
00:08:31,420 --> 00:08:33,340
I can lie down and sit if I want to.

152
00:08:33,540 --> 00:08:36,540
If I want to eat, I lean sideways
because lying down makes me hungry.

153
00:08:37,780 --> 00:08:38,780
In short,

154
00:08:38,780 --> 00:08:39,700
now I no longer

155
00:08:39,700 --> 00:08:40,800
have to please the seven or eight

156
00:08:40,800 --> 00:08:42,860
bosses and co-workers.

157
00:08:42,900 --> 00:08:44,340
All I need to please

158
00:08:44,340 --> 00:08:46,420
is the 100 or so people in the audience.

159
00:08:46,700 --> 00:08:48,300
Thank you, everyone! I'm Xiuya.

160
00:08:48,300 --> 00:08:51,210
Bravo!

161
00:09:09,300 --> 00:09:10,140
What happened to you?

162
00:09:12,900 --> 00:09:13,860
Nothing,

163
00:09:14,780 --> 00:09:16,300
I just remembered Xiuya...

164
00:09:23,180 --> 00:09:25,180
That kid performed pretty well.

165
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:30,640
(The First Stand-Up Comedy Audition)

166
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:31,500
At the store,

167
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:33,420
they gave me a pretty
expensive box of medicine

168
00:09:33,700 --> 00:09:35,980
and said it was a special remedy,
fast-acting.

169
00:09:37,100 --> 00:09:38,780
When I saw the price,

170
00:09:40,340 --> 00:09:41,260
I thought,

171
00:09:41,710 --> 00:09:42,980
"Well, I'm not in that much of a rush."

172
00:09:44,540 --> 00:09:45,680
The doctor told me

173
00:09:45,680 --> 00:09:47,660
to avoid certain foods like leftovers,
hot pot, and seafood,

174
00:09:47,660 --> 00:09:49,420
which are some of the biggest triggers

175
00:09:49,420 --> 00:09:50,700
for high uric acid and gout.

176
00:09:50,700 --> 00:09:51,700
I can't eat them anymore.

177
00:09:51,740 --> 00:09:52,700
I was freaking out.

178
00:09:52,700 --> 00:09:54,440
Just the other night,
I made a spicy seafood hot pot

179
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:55,420
with leftover broth.

180
00:09:57,420 --> 00:09:59,220
It was not supposed to raise uric acid.

181
00:09:59,220 --> 00:10:00,540
It was basically a pot of spicy,

182
00:10:00,540 --> 00:10:01,380
high-uric-acid soup.

183
00:10:02,700 --> 00:10:03,980
"You have such great style.

184
00:10:05,100 --> 00:10:07,100
Your skin is so smooth.

185
00:10:07,900 --> 00:10:09,700
Your figure is amazing."

186
00:10:09,700 --> 00:10:12,220
But it's all fake. None of it's real.

187
00:10:12,300 --> 00:10:13,700
My dad told me, "Son,

188
00:10:13,860 --> 00:10:14,900
choose this one.

189
00:10:15,300 --> 00:10:17,220
If you study this major well,

190
00:10:17,340 --> 00:10:19,700
you'll always have food to eat."

191
00:10:19,700 --> 00:10:22,420
Her actual boyfriend broke up with her.

192
00:10:24,540 --> 00:10:26,180
But you don't need
to feel sorry for me,

193
00:10:27,020 --> 00:10:28,440
because none of you

194
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:29,420
are feeling sorry for me.

195
00:10:30,060 --> 00:10:31,760
Then, after everyone else
was done yelling,

196
00:10:31,820 --> 00:10:33,940
I was there in the corner,
ranting intermittently,

197
00:10:34,700 --> 00:10:36,940
and they were beating me up
the same way.

198
00:10:38,940 --> 00:10:40,180
My mom didn't even notice

199
00:10:40,180 --> 00:10:41,700
this ad on the bottle that said,

200
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:44,940
"Fragrance is a woman's coat
of confidence."

201
00:10:46,020 --> 00:10:47,150
I thought that bottle of shower gel

202
00:10:47,150 --> 00:10:48,940
was calling me, "Come on,

203
00:10:49,380 --> 00:10:50,540
let's be women together!"

204
00:10:51,260 --> 00:10:53,620
After every show,
it's always close to midnight,

205
00:10:54,700 --> 00:10:55,700
and halfway home

206
00:10:56,310 --> 00:10:57,420
I always run out of battery.

207
00:10:57,700 --> 00:10:59,140
"Can I cut in line?

208
00:10:59,180 --> 00:11:01,060
I know Zhao, the director
of your department."

209
00:11:01,060 --> 00:11:02,940
With all that confidence he has,

210
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:05,540
our director feels insecure next to him.

211
00:11:06,700 --> 00:11:09,060
Standing on the stage
doing stand-up comedy,

212
00:11:09,380 --> 00:11:13,140
I can actually fulfill my dream
of earning money while standing.

213
00:11:14,020 --> 00:11:16,020
At least I didn't kneel.

214
00:11:17,500 --> 00:11:19,060
Thank you, everyone, I'm Yong.

215
00:11:22,660 --> 00:11:26,380
(The First Stand-Up Comedy Audition)

216
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:28,300
Congratulations on advancing!

217
00:11:28,460 --> 00:11:30,440
- Thank you!
- Congratulations on our elimination!

218
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:31,220
Come on.

219
00:11:33,300 --> 00:11:34,700
Ya is amazing.

220
00:11:39,540 --> 00:11:40,620
Give me some corn.

221
00:11:40,940 --> 00:11:41,780
Here you are.

222
00:11:42,380 --> 00:11:44,300
- Thanks.
- Take whatever you want.

223
00:11:44,300 --> 00:11:45,140
Okay.

224
00:11:45,940 --> 00:11:47,300
(During the Operation)

225
00:11:58,260 --> 00:12:00,780
(Compassionate, Virtuous,
Sensible, Knowledgeable)

226
00:12:25,820 --> 00:12:26,820
Don't worry,

227
00:12:27,140 --> 00:12:28,380
the surgery went very well.

228
00:12:28,820 --> 00:12:30,140
Just take good care afterward.

229
00:12:30,140 --> 00:12:30,980
Alright.

230
00:12:31,040 --> 00:12:32,020
Thank you, Director Wang.

231
00:12:32,020 --> 00:12:32,940
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

232
00:12:38,380 --> 00:12:39,220
Dad.

233
00:12:43,700 --> 00:12:46,860
(Xiaolan: The surgery went well!)

234
00:13:03,940 --> 00:13:04,780
Xiuya.

235
00:13:05,300 --> 00:13:06,260
Your mom's awake!

236
00:13:08,700 --> 00:13:09,540
Mom.

237
00:13:11,540 --> 00:13:12,620
How do you feel?

238
00:13:13,900 --> 00:13:17,700
(The First Stand-Up Comedy
16-to-8 Elimination Stage)

239
00:13:19,820 --> 00:13:20,940
You know,

240
00:13:21,180 --> 00:13:23,060
a marriage proposal is the only thing

241
00:13:23,060 --> 00:13:25,020
you can accomplish by kneeling.

242
00:13:25,020 --> 00:13:27,420
You can't get the same result
by praying in a temple.

243
00:13:28,420 --> 00:13:29,820
Public proposals, though,

244
00:13:29,820 --> 00:13:31,540
feel like moral blackmail.

245
00:13:31,540 --> 00:13:34,020
Such blackmail should be used
in more practical places.

246
00:13:34,020 --> 00:13:35,540
(Wu Xiuya, advanced)
For example, on bosses...

247
00:13:35,540 --> 00:13:38,300
Some hotels call their rooms
"ocean view"

248
00:13:38,500 --> 00:13:39,700
when they clearly aren't.

249
00:13:39,700 --> 00:13:40,900
I opened the door

250
00:13:40,900 --> 00:13:42,780
and the first thing I asked was,

251
00:13:43,180 --> 00:13:44,180
"Where's the ocean?"

252
00:13:44,640 --> 00:13:46,460
I was watching a construction site
outside the balcony.

253
00:13:46,460 --> 00:13:47,300
And I thought,

254
00:13:47,420 --> 00:13:49,900
(Meng'en, advanced)
"Did they fill it in at night?"

255
00:13:50,900 --> 00:13:51,980
The other day, I went out to eat,

256
00:13:51,980 --> 00:13:53,700
and at the table next to me,
there were four girls.

257
00:13:53,780 --> 00:13:55,180
One was wearing a zebra print,

258
00:13:55,180 --> 00:13:56,540
another a cow print,

259
00:13:56,540 --> 00:13:57,820
one had a tiger-striped tank top,

260
00:13:57,820 --> 00:13:59,540
and the last one
had a leopard print dress.

261
00:13:59,700 --> 00:14:01,820
I said, "Is this your animal-themed

262
00:14:01,820 --> 00:14:02,660
team-building event?

263
00:14:02,700 --> 00:14:03,940
Or a dress code

264
00:14:03,940 --> 00:14:05,300
of animal?"

265
00:14:07,460 --> 00:14:09,540
If you're not doing well in life,
maybe it's time to come back.

266
00:14:10,060 --> 00:14:11,700
You're not even 35 yet,

267
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:13,540
you still have a chance.

268
00:14:13,700 --> 00:14:16,180
- So the message is already mine, right?
- Yes.

269
00:14:16,180 --> 00:14:18,420
- And the phone's mine, right?
- Yes.

270
00:14:18,420 --> 00:14:20,180
Then why is he taking stuff

271
00:14:20,180 --> 00:14:21,940
(Shi Ye, advanced)
on my phone from me?

272
00:14:21,940 --> 00:14:23,060
Right!

