552
00:24:47,380 --> 00:24:48,620
and keep running Banghe.

553
00:24:49,420 --> 00:24:51,700
You're quite persuasive.

554
00:24:52,340 --> 00:24:54,340
But the person earlier

555
00:24:54,340 --> 00:24:56,860
gave me an even better reason.

556
00:24:59,900 --> 00:25:01,900
I'll add 1,000 more each month.

557
00:25:02,620 --> 00:25:03,460
Sorry,

558
00:25:03,700 --> 00:25:05,140
I've decided to rent

559
00:25:05,140 --> 00:25:06,420
to the other team after all.

560
00:25:06,580 --> 00:25:08,420
I'm more familiar with them

561
00:25:08,820 --> 00:25:09,940
and I trust them more.

562
00:25:10,620 --> 00:25:11,700
Today's treat is on me.

563
00:25:11,700 --> 00:25:12,940
Don't worry about it.

564
00:25:14,700 --> 00:25:16,580
They offered a higher price than mine?

565
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:20,030
It's fine, this still counts as mine.

566
00:25:20,030 --> 00:25:21,060
I'll go talk to them.

567
00:25:21,940 --> 00:25:22,780
No,

568
00:25:23,180 --> 00:25:24,020
wait.

569
00:25:24,420 --> 00:25:26,060
Hey, wait.

570
00:25:26,100 --> 00:25:27,180
Don't rush.

571
00:25:27,180 --> 00:25:28,900
We work so well together.

572
00:25:29,060 --> 00:25:31,180
Convincing with reason,
persuading with money.

573
00:25:31,700 --> 00:25:32,820
Clever!

574
00:25:34,180 --> 00:25:35,460
Why are you walking so fast?

575
00:25:35,620 --> 00:25:37,700
Why are you in such a hurry?

576
00:25:38,620 --> 00:25:39,460
Bro,

577
00:25:39,620 --> 00:25:41,180
let me tell you,

578
00:25:41,180 --> 00:25:42,700
the two girls are gonna be scared.

579
00:25:45,900 --> 00:25:48,340
So it was you
competing with us for the bar?

580
00:25:48,860 --> 00:25:50,900
You guys know each other?

581
00:25:52,940 --> 00:25:53,780
Well, then,

582
00:25:53,790 --> 00:25:55,420
how about we all talk it out?

583
00:25:55,860 --> 00:25:57,380
Fine, go ahead and talk,

584
00:25:57,620 --> 00:25:58,580
I'll head up.

585
00:25:58,860 --> 00:25:59,700
Take it out.

586
00:26:02,700 --> 00:26:03,540
Wait,

587
00:26:03,900 --> 00:26:06,180
Zheng Hao, why are you causing trouble?

588
00:26:06,900 --> 00:26:09,460
Watch your words, I'm investing.

589
00:26:10,080 --> 00:26:11,180
What do you mean, causing trouble?

590
00:26:11,220 --> 00:26:13,340
You can invest wherever you want,

591
00:26:13,340 --> 00:26:15,140
but why are you competing
with us for Banghe?

592
00:26:15,140 --> 00:26:16,700
- Right.
- I didn't expect you two

593
00:26:16,700 --> 00:26:18,180
to be the competitors.

594
00:26:20,700 --> 00:26:21,760
Well, since it's like this,

595
00:26:22,180 --> 00:26:23,380
I have a suggestion.

596
00:26:23,860 --> 00:26:24,760
How about

597
00:26:24,760 --> 00:26:26,530
the three of us
investing in Banghe together?

598
00:26:26,620 --> 00:26:28,420
We can all be shareholders.

599
00:26:29,100 --> 00:26:30,180
That's possible,

600
00:26:30,700 --> 00:26:32,700
but can you two still work together

601
00:26:32,700 --> 00:26:33,940
given your history?

602
00:26:34,700 --> 00:26:35,860
I'm fine with it.

603
00:26:35,860 --> 00:26:36,940
Me too.

604
00:26:37,100 --> 00:26:38,900
I think cooperation is a good idea,

605
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:39,820
and I trust Zheng Hao's

606
00:26:39,820 --> 00:26:40,900
business acumen.

607
00:26:41,700 --> 00:26:43,700
Okay, let's do it.

608
00:26:44,900 --> 00:26:47,180
But the price just went up.

609
00:26:47,180 --> 00:26:48,020
What to do?

610
00:26:48,620 --> 00:26:49,820
This isn't very cost-effective.

611
00:26:49,940 --> 00:26:50,780
Don't worry,

612
00:26:51,180 --> 00:26:52,020
I've got a plan.

613
00:26:56,310 --> 00:26:58,870
♪Shanghai, the bustling metropolis♪

614
00:26:58,870 --> 00:27:01,590
♪Running to catch the bus♪

615
00:27:01,590 --> 00:27:04,140
♪Crowded with people everywhere♪

616
00:27:04,140 --> 00:27:06,860
♪Watch your step in the daily spree♪

617
00:27:06,860 --> 00:27:09,420
♪Packed subways and endless tunnels♪

618
00:27:09,420 --> 00:27:12,100
♪Riding an F1 to go to the stock market♪

619
00:27:12,620 --> 00:27:13,460
Wait a minute.

620
00:27:13,620 --> 00:27:15,420
What we just agreed on,

621
00:27:15,900 --> 00:27:18,340
are you guys going to back out?

622
00:27:18,340 --> 00:27:19,700
Of course not.

623
00:27:20,140 --> 00:27:22,700
In business, timing is everything,

624
00:27:22,700 --> 00:27:24,340
and we have to adjust our offers

625
00:27:24,340 --> 00:27:25,900
according to the situation.

626
00:27:25,900 --> 00:27:28,340
You know better than anyone else
about the situation.

627
00:27:28,340 --> 00:27:29,700
Right. To be honest,

628
00:27:29,900 --> 00:27:30,820
your location

629
00:27:30,820 --> 00:27:32,420
is not really in a prime area.

630
00:27:32,420 --> 00:27:34,320
It's far from commercial zones,
office districts

631
00:27:34,320 --> 00:27:35,740
and places

632
00:27:35,740 --> 00:27:36,990
where high-income groups gather.

633
00:27:36,990 --> 00:27:38,180
Any business here

634
00:27:38,820 --> 00:27:40,340
will struggle to attract traffic.

635
00:27:40,420 --> 00:27:41,600
If we both pull out,

636
00:27:41,600 --> 00:27:43,310
you'll be left waiting
for the next tenant,

637
00:27:43,310 --> 00:27:44,900
and that could take months.

638
00:27:44,900 --> 00:27:45,820
If this place is vacant

639
00:27:45,820 --> 00:27:47,380
for two months,

640
00:27:47,380 --> 00:27:48,460
all the extra

641
00:27:48,460 --> 00:27:49,420
rent we added

642
00:27:49,420 --> 00:27:50,700
will be for nothing.

643
00:27:50,700 --> 00:27:51,620
Maybe even worse,

644
00:27:51,620 --> 00:27:53,420
if it takes six months to rent out,

645
00:27:53,420 --> 00:27:54,900
you'll lose a lot.

646
00:27:54,900 --> 00:27:56,420
Of course, we're not going to be

647
00:27:56,420 --> 00:27:57,280
unreasonable.

648
00:27:57,280 --> 00:27:59,620
We'll still offer the extra 10% rent

649
00:27:59,620 --> 00:28:00,900
as we agreed before.

650
00:28:01,510 --> 00:28:03,490
- We'll pay every six months.
- What do you think?

651
00:28:05,700 --> 00:28:06,820
What do I think?

652
00:28:08,140 --> 00:28:09,140
Honestly,

653
00:28:10,460 --> 00:28:11,900
I can't argue with the three of you.

654
00:28:12,940 --> 00:28:13,780
Then...

655
00:28:14,420 --> 00:28:16,700
Alright, then let's go with your offer.

656
00:28:17,060 --> 00:28:17,900
We'll

657
00:28:19,420 --> 00:28:20,380
sign today.

658
00:28:20,380 --> 00:28:21,270
♪Let me, let me♪

659
00:28:21,270 --> 00:28:23,210
♪Shanghai, let me toast you a cup♪

660
00:28:23,700 --> 00:28:24,540
How about

661
00:28:24,580 --> 00:28:25,900
I tell you a little joke

662
00:28:25,900 --> 00:28:26,900
to make you happy?

663
00:28:28,180 --> 00:28:29,140
Taking advantage of me

664
00:28:29,340 --> 00:28:30,900
and then planning to make fun of me?

665
00:28:31,340 --> 00:28:32,180
Forget it.

666
00:28:33,420 --> 00:28:34,900
What to do now?

667
00:28:35,340 --> 00:28:36,180
Shall we sign?

668
00:28:36,340 --> 00:28:37,180
Let's sign!

669
00:28:49,060 --> 00:28:51,460
From now on, this place is ours.

670
00:28:56,420 --> 00:28:57,700
I've made a business plan

671
00:28:57,900 --> 00:28:59,220
for Banghe.

672
00:28:59,220 --> 00:29:00,260
Let's take a look together

673
00:29:00,260 --> 00:29:01,110
and discuss it later.

674
00:29:02,380 --> 00:29:04,180
This is a brand new beginning.

675
00:29:04,660 --> 00:29:06,020
(Three-year Profit Plan)
Hold on, I think

676
00:29:06,020 --> 00:29:08,190
(Conditions to Achieve Profitability)
you misunderstood the focus.

677
00:29:08,190 --> 00:29:10,180
This isn't just a bar.

678
00:29:10,180 --> 00:29:11,420
We should tell everyone

679
00:29:11,420 --> 00:29:13,060
that it's a stand-up comedy bar.

680
00:29:13,110 --> 00:29:15,150
The point is, people come here
for the performances.

681
00:29:15,150 --> 00:29:16,140
- Right.
- Okay.

682
00:29:16,140 --> 00:29:18,420
So let's not call it Banghe Bar.

683
00:29:18,420 --> 00:29:19,700
We'll call it Banghe Comedy Club.

684
00:29:19,700 --> 00:29:20,700
How about that?

685
00:29:27,240 --> 00:29:28,740
The drinks have to be
good-looking and tasty.

686
00:29:28,740 --> 00:29:30,460
Exactly. Leave that to her
to figure out.

687
00:29:35,420 --> 00:29:36,340
Look here.

688
00:29:36,900 --> 00:29:38,140
Three, two, one.

689
00:29:40,780 --> 00:29:41,700
(Inpatient Department)

690
00:29:41,700 --> 00:29:43,180
Mom, what do you want to eat later?

691
00:29:44,620 --> 00:29:45,580
Try my cooking.

692
00:29:45,580 --> 00:29:46,420
Here.

693
00:29:47,180 --> 00:29:48,020
How is it?

694
00:29:48,860 --> 00:29:49,700
What's wrong?

695
00:29:49,900 --> 00:29:50,740
It's way too sweet!

696
00:29:51,100 --> 00:29:51,940
That can't be!

697
00:29:53,580 --> 00:29:54,420
Try it again.

698
00:29:58,100 --> 00:29:58,940
Oh no,

699
00:29:59,700 --> 00:30:01,180
I accidentally swapped sugar for salt!

700
00:30:02,580 --> 00:30:03,820
Come on, I'll make it again.

701
00:30:04,900 --> 00:30:06,580
Let's just order takeout.

702
00:30:12,140 --> 00:30:12,980
Shi Ye.

703
00:30:13,140 --> 00:30:13,980
Shi Ye?

704
00:30:17,460 --> 00:30:18,340
Uncle, Auntie.

705
00:30:19,420 --> 00:30:20,700
We have a favor to ask.

706
00:30:21,180 --> 00:30:22,060
What is it?

707
00:30:22,240 --> 00:30:24,050
We need to borrow
your caravan for a few days.

708
00:30:25,180 --> 00:30:26,020
No problem.

709
00:30:26,460 --> 00:30:29,680
(The First Stand-Up Comedy Audition)
Welcome to the semi-finals

710
00:30:29,680 --> 00:30:30,700
of our comedy competition.

711
00:30:30,820 --> 00:30:31,700
Honestly,

712
00:30:32,580 --> 00:30:33,900
I never expected

713
00:30:33,900 --> 00:30:35,820
we'd make it this far.

714
00:30:37,570 --> 00:30:38,420
Normally,

715
00:30:38,420 --> 00:30:40,620
sponsors would pull out

716
00:30:40,620 --> 00:30:41,580
after the second round,

717
00:30:43,110 --> 00:30:44,900
so we need to thank
everyone here especially.

718
00:30:45,100 --> 00:30:47,180
Because you performed so well here,

719
00:30:47,900 --> 00:30:50,700
those who were watching the show
on their phones

720
00:30:50,700 --> 00:30:52,180
thought our performers

721
00:30:52,180 --> 00:30:53,700
were really funny.

722
00:30:54,580 --> 00:30:55,900
So, whether or not

723
00:30:55,900 --> 00:30:56,900
we have a final,

724
00:30:56,900 --> 00:30:58,100
I sincerely invite everyone

725
00:30:58,100 --> 00:30:59,420
to join the next event

726
00:30:59,420 --> 00:31:00,580
organized by our committee,

727
00:31:00,580 --> 00:31:02,180
called "I Am the Actor".

728
00:31:02,820 --> 00:31:05,140
You've all made it to the finals.

729
00:31:05,140 --> 00:31:07,180
We look forward to your
more wonderful performances.

730
00:31:07,240 --> 00:31:09,090
The semi-finalists
are divided into two groups,

731
00:31:09,090 --> 00:31:10,210
competing against each other.

732
00:31:10,340 --> 00:31:13,340
In the first group,
we have Wu Xiuya versus Shi Ye,

733
00:31:13,340 --> 00:31:16,180
and in the second group,
Wang Jin versus Pang Bo.

734
00:31:16,220 --> 00:31:17,700
Let's welcome

735
00:31:17,860 --> 00:31:19,940
the first contestant of the first group,

736
00:31:19,940 --> 00:31:21,180
Shi Ye, please welcome him!

737
00:31:35,110 --> 00:31:36,180
Hello everyone, I'm Shi Ye.

738
00:31:39,340 --> 00:31:40,260
Recently, I've realized

739
00:31:40,260 --> 00:31:41,700
that communication between people

740
00:31:41,700 --> 00:31:43,140
isn't really about the content,

741
00:31:43,700 --> 00:31:44,940
it's about the emotions.

742
00:31:45,180 --> 00:31:46,620
Xiuya, you can wait here.

743
00:31:46,740 --> 00:31:48,420
- You're next.
- Thanks.

744
00:31:48,500 --> 00:31:49,420
Just tell them,

745
00:31:49,500 --> 00:31:51,140
"You're absolutely right."

746
00:31:51,980 --> 00:31:53,500
If you hear someone complaining,

747
00:31:53,520 --> 00:31:54,460
no matter what they say,

748
00:31:54,480 --> 00:31:55,380
just tell them,

749
00:31:55,500 --> 00:31:57,380
"How can he be like this?"

750
00:31:58,060 --> 00:31:59,620
If they seem really sad,

751
00:31:59,700 --> 00:32:01,420
you just say, "You're a person

752
00:32:01,500 --> 00:32:03,100
with too many feelings."

753
00:32:04,580 --> 00:32:05,460
Friends,

754
00:32:05,460 --> 00:32:06,820
if you learn these three sentences,

755
00:32:06,820 --> 00:32:08,180
you can go anywhere without fear.

756
00:32:08,180 --> 00:32:09,900
Even if your girlfriend
breaks up with you.

757
00:32:09,960 --> 00:32:11,700
Just like my ex-girlfriend
broke up with me.

758
00:32:11,700 --> 00:32:12,860
She said, "Shi Ye, let's break up."

759
00:32:13,060 --> 00:32:13,900
And I said,

760
00:32:13,910 --> 00:32:15,700
"You're absolutely right."

761
00:32:28,180 --> 00:32:29,980
I said, "You're absolutely right."

762
00:32:29,980 --> 00:32:31,820
I'm the one he just talked about.

763
00:32:32,100 --> 00:32:33,140
Let me explain this.

764
00:32:33,140 --> 00:32:34,140
You sit down for a while.

765
00:32:35,980 --> 00:32:36,980
Let's break up.

766
00:32:38,060 --> 00:32:39,740
You're absolutely right.

767
00:32:45,940 --> 00:32:46,780
Wait,

768
00:32:46,860 --> 00:32:48,420
I suddenly feel

769
00:32:48,820 --> 00:32:50,260
that since she's already my ex,

770
00:32:50,420 --> 00:32:52,420
it might not be right
to make fun of her.

771
00:32:53,060 --> 00:32:55,380
Also, from her perspective,

772
00:32:55,700 --> 00:32:57,700
I must have been
quite unbearable as well.

773
00:32:57,980 --> 00:33:00,180
I used to think of myself

774
00:33:00,420 --> 00:33:01,500
as an honest person,

775
00:33:01,740 --> 00:33:02,620
because

776
00:33:02,700 --> 00:33:04,620
before I started dating a girl,

777
00:33:04,700 --> 00:33:05,860
I would always tell her

778
00:33:06,100 --> 00:33:07,380
that I was against marriage.

779
00:33:07,940 --> 00:33:09,180
If she agreed,

780
00:33:09,180 --> 00:33:10,180
then we'd date.

781
00:33:10,380 --> 00:33:11,210
I brought it up

782
00:33:11,210 --> 00:33:12,180
not for any other reason,

783
00:33:12,180 --> 00:33:13,620
but because I wanted

784
00:33:13,620 --> 00:33:14,700
a pure love.

785
00:33:15,140 --> 00:33:15,980
I wanted us

786
00:33:15,980 --> 00:33:17,280
to follow our hearts

787
00:33:17,290 --> 00:33:18,280
and not let anything else

788
00:33:18,280 --> 00:33:20,220
tie down our emotions.

789
00:33:20,980 --> 00:33:22,420
But recently, I realized,

790
00:33:22,700 --> 00:33:25,260
if you look at it from
the girl's perspective,

791
00:33:25,900 --> 00:33:27,180
my anti-marriage stance

792
00:33:27,420 --> 00:33:28,900
actually ruined the purity.

793
00:33:28,980 --> 00:33:30,900
You're both sure you won't marry,

794
00:33:30,900 --> 00:33:32,980
so where can this relationship go?

795
00:33:33,520 --> 00:33:34,380
It's like,

796
00:33:34,380 --> 00:33:35,870
from the very beginning
of this relationship,

797
00:33:35,870 --> 00:33:37,420
there's a time bomb

798
00:33:37,900 --> 00:33:39,180
ticking away

799
00:33:39,900 --> 00:33:41,420
and you're still trying

800
00:33:41,420 --> 00:33:43,100
to have a pure romance.

801
00:33:43,680 --> 00:33:44,540
That's only in movies.

802
00:33:45,940 --> 00:33:46,980
I finally realized

803
00:33:47,740 --> 00:33:48,900
the purity I wanted

804
00:33:49,700 --> 00:33:50,860
was actually

805
00:33:51,260 --> 00:33:52,700
rejecting the real world.

806
00:33:55,420 --> 00:33:56,820
Behind that was my own cowardice.

807
00:33:57,820 --> 00:33:59,060
I was afraid of

808
00:33:59,220 --> 00:34:00,820
the real challenges in life,

809
00:34:01,180 --> 00:34:02,110
conflicts,

810
00:34:02,800 --> 00:34:03,940
and the complexity of human nature.

811
00:34:08,220 --> 00:34:10,380
I felt really down

812
00:34:11,180 --> 00:34:12,180
when I realized all this.

813
00:34:13,340 --> 00:34:15,380
Because I always thought
of myself as someone

814
00:34:15,420 --> 00:34:16,820
who wasn't bound by society's norms,

815
00:34:17,180 --> 00:34:19,140
who bravely
pursued freedom and purity.

816
00:34:20,060 --> 00:34:22,180
But in the end, I realized,

817
00:34:22,180 --> 00:34:23,020
I am

818
00:34:23,180 --> 00:34:24,180
the biggest obstacle

819
00:34:24,420 --> 00:34:25,820
to myself.

820
00:34:27,860 --> 00:34:29,140
I was depressed for many days,

821
00:34:30,180 --> 00:34:31,180
and I kept

822
00:34:32,140 --> 00:34:33,900
thinking about my ex.

823
00:34:34,420 --> 00:34:36,900
I watched her go
from a carefree, bold girl

824
00:34:37,100 --> 00:34:38,140
to someone

825
00:34:38,140 --> 00:34:39,700
trying to please everyone.

826
00:34:40,180 --> 00:34:41,190
And then, she courageously

827
00:34:41,190 --> 00:34:42,700
reclaimed herself.

828
00:34:45,340 --> 00:34:46,180
I understood

829
00:34:47,140 --> 00:34:48,700
that courage isn't something

830
00:34:49,180 --> 00:34:50,700
you have once and for all.

831
00:34:52,180 --> 00:34:53,180
It's a consumable,

832
00:34:53,900 --> 00:34:55,700
you have to keep recharging it.

833
00:34:56,420 --> 00:34:57,900
Life is scary like that.

834
00:34:58,100 --> 00:35:00,340
Even those who are wealthy,

835
00:35:00,460 --> 00:35:01,460
those who are strong,

836
00:35:01,700 --> 00:35:03,940
those who are calm and carefree,

837
00:35:04,220 --> 00:35:06,420
those with strong willpower,

838
00:35:06,580 --> 00:35:08,420
they all face

839
00:35:08,420 --> 00:35:09,900
fears big and small.

840
00:35:10,420 --> 00:35:11,580
Real courage is the ability

841
00:35:12,140 --> 00:35:14,060
to keep gathering courage

842
00:35:14,140 --> 00:35:15,900
and fighting against your own fear.

843
00:35:16,900 --> 00:35:19,340
Life is a constant process
of depleting courage

844
00:35:19,420 --> 00:35:21,180
and then finding the courage again.

845
00:35:21,940 --> 00:35:23,460
As Romain Rolland said,

846
00:35:24,180 --> 00:35:25,730
"There is only one heroism in the world:

847
00:35:25,860 --> 00:35:27,860
to see the world as it is

848
00:35:28,180 --> 00:35:29,420
and to love it."

849
00:35:31,700 --> 00:35:32,540
Thank you, everyone.

850
00:35:33,220 --> 00:35:34,140
I'm Shi Ye.

851
00:35:39,060 --> 00:35:46,060
(The First Stand-Up Comedy Audition)

852
00:35:54,940 --> 00:35:58,580
(Wu Xiuya, blocked)

853
00:36:03,700 --> 00:36:05,700
Each of them has their strengths.

854
00:36:05,980 --> 00:36:08,020
Also, did you notice
how long their legs are?

855
00:36:09,180 --> 00:36:11,180
They are indeed all very talented

856
00:36:11,180 --> 00:36:12,180
stand-up comedians,

857
00:36:12,180 --> 00:36:14,580
but there are only two spots

858
00:36:14,580 --> 00:36:15,540
left in the finals.

859
00:36:16,020 --> 00:36:17,180
So

860
00:36:18,060 --> 00:36:20,180
which two will make it to the finals

861
00:36:20,180 --> 00:36:25,020
of the First National
Stand-Up Comedy Audition?

862
00:36:25,180 --> 00:36:26,700
Let's see the big screen.

863
00:36:27,580 --> 00:36:30,700
(Pang Bo, Wu Xiuya)
Pang Bo! Pang Bo!

864
00:36:30,940 --> 00:36:31,940
Congratulations!

865
00:36:32,980 --> 00:36:35,140
Congratulations to Wu Xiuya and Pang Bo

866
00:36:35,140 --> 00:36:36,300
for advancing to the finals!

867
00:36:37,220 --> 00:36:39,420
At the same time, we'd like
to thank Wang Jin and Shi Ye

868
00:36:39,420 --> 00:36:41,700
for bringing us
such wonderful performances.

869
00:36:41,700 --> 00:36:42,540
Thank you!

870
00:36:42,620 --> 00:36:44,740
Please stay tuned to the final.

871
00:36:44,740 --> 00:36:45,620
Thank you, audience.

872
00:36:45,620 --> 00:36:47,460
Please exit in an orderly manner.
Thank you.

873
00:37:17,260 --> 00:37:18,140
Congratulations.

874
00:37:19,700 --> 00:37:20,540
Thank you.

875
00:37:22,020 --> 00:37:23,700
If you tell the original joke,

876
00:37:24,020 --> 00:37:26,260
now I should be the one
congratulating you.

877
00:37:29,540 --> 00:37:30,940
What you said just now,

878
00:37:31,780 --> 00:37:33,140
"Courage isn't something you have

879
00:37:33,140 --> 00:37:34,580
once and for all."

880
00:37:34,700 --> 00:37:36,060
I think you're absolutely right.

881
00:37:37,740 --> 00:37:39,940
That part was impromptu, right?

882
00:37:42,220 --> 00:37:43,180
No punchline.

883
00:37:44,020 --> 00:37:45,460
You knew it might not be funny,

884
00:37:45,460 --> 00:37:46,740
so why did you still say it?

885
00:37:49,180 --> 00:37:51,060
Who says stand-up comedy
has to be funny?

886
00:37:52,100 --> 00:37:53,020
Do you remember why we

887
00:37:53,020 --> 00:37:54,340
first liked stand-up comedy?

888
00:37:54,980 --> 00:37:56,260
Was it just because it's funny?

889
00:37:57,620 --> 00:37:59,580
No, it's because
in stand-up comedy jokes,

890
00:37:59,860 --> 00:38:01,100
there are always hidden messages

891
00:38:01,100 --> 00:38:02,300
from deep within us.

892
00:38:03,100 --> 00:38:04,700
Just now, on stage, I suddenly

893
00:38:06,080 --> 00:38:07,260
had something I wanted to say.

894
00:38:11,460 --> 00:38:12,700
For what you just said,

895
00:38:13,700 --> 00:38:14,700
in my heart,

896
00:38:14,700 --> 00:38:16,700
you've already won against me.

897
00:38:24,700 --> 00:38:25,600
Actually,

898
00:38:25,600 --> 00:38:27,220
I've been really
disappointed in myself recently.

899
00:38:27,500 --> 00:38:30,140
I thought I'd be
much stronger than before,

900
00:38:31,580 --> 00:38:33,180
but I overestimated myself.

901
00:38:34,740 --> 00:38:36,180
Even with stand-up comedy,

902
00:38:36,260 --> 00:38:37,220
when I face tough times,

903
00:38:37,220 --> 00:38:38,740
I still break down.

904
00:38:38,740 --> 00:38:40,020
I still can't get past it.

905
00:38:41,340 --> 00:38:42,980
I used to tell myself,

906
00:38:44,140 --> 00:38:46,180
all these messy things in life

907
00:38:47,700 --> 00:38:48,940
are actually wealth,

908
00:38:49,540 --> 00:38:50,540
material for comedy.

909
00:38:50,780 --> 00:38:52,180
Just turn them into jokes,

910
00:38:52,180 --> 00:38:53,100
laugh it off,

911
00:38:53,100 --> 00:38:54,260
and it'll all pass.

912
00:38:54,940 --> 00:38:56,260
But I still can't do it.

913
00:39:00,100 --> 00:39:01,340
Stand-up comedy isn't a cure.

914
00:39:04,020 --> 00:39:04,860
Right.

915
00:39:06,620 --> 00:39:08,180
What you said woke me up.

916
00:39:09,260 --> 00:39:10,140
Thank you.

917
00:39:10,700 --> 00:39:11,780
Don't thank me.

918
00:39:12,620 --> 00:39:13,460
Thank your mom.

919
00:39:15,820 --> 00:39:17,620
Recently, your mom chatted with me.

920
00:39:17,780 --> 00:39:18,980
What did she talk to you about?

921
00:39:20,740 --> 00:39:21,580
Don't tell me

922
00:39:21,980 --> 00:39:23,980
she wants you and me
to get back together.

923
00:39:25,100 --> 00:39:26,580
You really underestimated her.

924
00:39:27,500 --> 00:39:28,340
She

925
00:39:28,580 --> 00:39:31,260
asked to borrow my caravan.

926
00:39:31,540 --> 00:39:33,540
Why did she ask to borrow your caravan?

927
00:39:34,060 --> 00:39:36,260
She and your dad want
to take the caravan

928
00:39:36,260 --> 00:39:37,580
and go on a nationwide trip.

929
00:39:38,340 --> 00:39:40,180
But she just had surgery, right?

930
00:39:40,260 --> 00:39:41,100
Yeah.

931
00:39:41,180 --> 00:39:43,260
She said she could recuperate anywhere.

932
00:39:43,780 --> 00:39:45,940
The bed in the caravan is still a bed.

933
00:39:46,340 --> 00:39:47,580
They want to drive it

934
00:39:47,580 --> 00:39:49,260
to beautiful places,

935
00:39:49,500 --> 00:39:51,540
see the sights, breathe fresh air,

936
00:39:51,700 --> 00:39:53,140
and every day is a new experience.

937
00:39:53,180 --> 00:39:55,060
Maybe that's better for her health.

938
00:39:56,900 --> 00:39:57,930
She also said

939
00:39:59,020 --> 00:40:00,260
this was her childhood dream.

940
00:40:01,460 --> 00:40:03,580
The life I hated the most

941
00:40:04,820 --> 00:40:07,460
was the kind where you
could see the end from the start.

942
00:40:08,180 --> 00:40:09,980
I wanted to break
out of those constraints.

943
00:40:11,180 --> 00:40:13,180
So, despite my parents' objections,

944
00:40:13,580 --> 00:40:15,180
I married Xiuya's father.

945
00:40:17,100 --> 00:40:18,140
But in the end,

946
00:40:18,700 --> 00:40:20,060
why should I blame him

947
00:40:20,060 --> 00:40:21,580
for constantly moving around?

948
00:40:21,700 --> 00:40:23,620
Wasn't that the life I wanted?

949
00:40:24,020 --> 00:40:25,700
I was trapped by what?

950
00:40:26,460 --> 00:40:27,300
My husband?

951
00:40:28,020 --> 00:40:28,940
My daughter?

952
00:40:29,380 --> 00:40:30,540
Or my parents?

953
00:40:34,700 --> 00:40:36,700
After this illness, I realized,

954
00:40:37,620 --> 00:40:39,940
I trapped myself.

955
00:40:40,780 --> 00:40:41,780
I got cancer,

956
00:40:42,460 --> 00:40:43,740
but does that mean I can't laugh,

957
00:40:44,540 --> 00:40:46,260
I can't travel the world?

958
00:40:48,300 --> 00:40:49,940
As long as I want that kind of life,

959
00:40:51,100 --> 00:40:52,780
I can always fight for it.

960
00:40:56,500 --> 00:40:57,340
In fact,

961
00:40:58,460 --> 00:40:59,740
I don't want that life

962
00:40:59,780 --> 00:41:01,540
where everything is predictable.

963
00:41:02,700 --> 00:41:04,540
I don't want to be constrained by rules.

964
00:41:05,700 --> 00:41:07,740
That's why I don't work, I don't marry.

965
00:41:08,820 --> 00:41:10,260
But later, I realized,

966
00:41:10,700 --> 00:41:11,780
without even knowing it,

967
00:41:12,180 --> 00:41:14,060
I was trapped in another kind of circle.

968
00:41:15,060 --> 00:41:17,020
True freedom and spontaneity

969
00:41:17,620 --> 00:41:19,700
mean opening to any possibility.

970
00:41:23,140 --> 00:41:24,700
What does that mean?

971
00:41:30,100 --> 00:41:31,180
I want to say,

972
00:41:33,540 --> 00:41:34,780
I regret breaking up with you.

973
00:41:45,980 --> 00:41:48,340
Actually, when you
brought up breaking up,

974
00:41:50,100 --> 00:41:51,700
it made me think a lot.

975
00:41:53,180 --> 00:41:54,780
What kind of relationship do I want?

976
00:41:54,780 --> 00:41:56,060
What kind of life do I want?

977
00:41:57,620 --> 00:41:58,940
I still haven't figured it out.

978
00:42:00,540 --> 00:42:04,260
So I think we still have plenty of
time and space to explore.

979
00:42:08,340 --> 00:42:09,260
The future

980
00:42:10,700 --> 00:42:12,180
will naturally become clear.

981
00:42:15,100 --> 00:42:15,940
Let's go.

982
00:42:16,820 --> 00:42:23,820
(The First Stand-Up Comedy Audition)

983
00:42:42,300 --> 00:42:43,140
Thank you.

984
00:42:43,500 --> 00:42:44,340
No problem.

985
00:42:45,340 --> 00:42:47,740
I came to talk to you about Banghe.

986
00:42:48,460 --> 00:42:50,580
Me, Xiuya and Xiaolan
have taken over Banghe.

987
00:42:50,580 --> 00:42:51,460
We want to run

988
00:42:51,460 --> 00:42:53,020
a more professional club.

989
00:42:53,700 --> 00:42:55,100
I think you're very talented.

990
00:42:56,180 --> 00:42:57,100
I know.

991
00:42:59,620 --> 00:43:00,700
But just a little weak.

992
00:43:05,060 --> 00:43:06,140
Your so-called anti-marriage

993
00:43:06,460 --> 00:43:07,860
is just a sign of weakness, right?

994
00:43:08,400 --> 00:43:10,870
You reject it in advance
because you're afraid of getting hurt.

995
00:43:12,300 --> 00:43:14,460
As for me, I went into
a relationship with Xiuya

996
00:43:14,460 --> 00:43:16,020
with the limitation of
"I want to get married."

997
00:43:16,020 --> 00:43:17,480
And you went
into the relationship with her

998
00:43:17,480 --> 00:43:19,240
with the limitation of
"I don't want to get married."

999
00:43:19,620 --> 00:43:21,700
In essence, there's no difference.

1000
00:43:22,380 --> 00:43:23,380
But I think

1001
00:43:23,860 --> 00:43:25,300
Xiuya shouldn't need this.

1002
00:43:26,030 --> 00:43:27,160
If the road is already paved,

1003
00:43:27,160 --> 00:43:28,820
what's the point
of just walking along it?

1004
00:43:29,220 --> 00:43:30,060
Life

1005
00:43:30,060 --> 00:43:32,100
should be like a vast grassland.

1006
00:43:32,260 --> 00:43:33,460
You should walk when you want

1007
00:43:33,460 --> 00:43:34,860
and stop when you want.

1008
00:43:39,220 --> 00:43:40,180
I've said

1009
00:43:41,700 --> 00:43:43,140
all this to Xiuya before.

1010
00:43:45,020 --> 00:43:47,460
Actually, what I wanted to ask you is

1011
00:43:48,140 --> 00:43:49,940
I think Banghe's stage needs you.

1012
00:43:50,300 --> 00:43:51,300
I want to sign you.

1013
00:43:57,680 --> 00:43:58,650
Help me wash the caravan.

1014
00:44:00,340 --> 00:44:01,180
Why?

1015
00:44:01,340 --> 00:44:02,340
We're quick together.

1016
00:44:02,740 --> 00:44:03,620
That makes sense.

1017
00:44:03,980 --> 00:44:05,700
So why don't you
take it to the car wash?

1018
00:44:05,940 --> 00:44:08,020
No money. Don't talk nonsense.

1019
00:44:08,020 --> 00:44:09,700
Afterwards, I still need
to give it to Xiuya's mom.

1020
00:44:14,500 --> 00:44:15,620
So will you come or not?

1021
00:44:16,180 --> 00:44:17,180
Come or not?

1022
00:44:17,180 --> 00:44:18,940
You make it sound
like Banghe is your home.

1023
00:44:19,700 --> 00:44:22,940
I'm one of the owners of Banghe now.

1024
00:44:23,300 --> 00:44:24,700
Of course Banghe is my home.

1025
00:44:25,060 --> 00:44:26,260
Then you're a stepfather.

1026
00:44:26,700 --> 00:44:28,020
But you're not a real dad either.

1027
00:44:28,020 --> 00:44:29,260
Yong is the real one.

1028
00:44:29,700 --> 00:44:30,640
Whatever father you are,

1029
00:44:30,640 --> 00:44:31,700
now you're mansplaining me.

1030
00:44:32,220 --> 00:44:33,740
You brought it up first.

1031
00:44:36,700 --> 00:44:37,540
By the way,

1032
00:44:37,550 --> 00:44:38,980
I need to tell you something.

1033
00:44:39,810 --> 00:44:40,980
I'm going to try to win Xiuya again.

1034
00:44:45,060 --> 00:44:46,620
Coincidentally, so am I.

1035
00:44:47,780 --> 00:44:48,620
Fair competition?

1036
00:44:49,700 --> 00:44:50,540
Fair competition.

1037
00:45:05,700 --> 00:45:06,540
Which table?

1038
00:45:06,700 --> 00:45:07,540
- Table 5.
- 5?

1039
00:45:11,700 --> 00:45:12,540
Hello.

1040
00:45:12,820 --> 00:45:13,660
You're here?

1041
00:45:13,700 --> 00:45:14,540
We'll be right there.

1042
00:45:15,000 --> 00:45:15,860
They are all here.

1043
00:45:15,860 --> 00:45:16,700
Okay.

1044
00:45:23,340 --> 00:45:24,540
Hello.

1045
00:45:28,260 --> 00:45:29,700
Thank you.

1046
00:45:29,700 --> 00:45:31,300
- Long time no see.
- Welcome.

1047
00:45:31,300 --> 00:45:32,180
Congratulations.

1048
00:45:32,500 --> 00:45:34,580
Grand opening!

1049
00:45:34,600 --> 00:45:35,900
- Wish you prosperity.
- Grand opening!

1050
00:45:35,900 --> 00:45:36,740
Everyone's here.

1051
00:45:36,740 --> 00:45:38,130
- Rolling in wealth!
- You've lost weight.

1052
00:45:38,130 --> 00:45:39,080
We even sent a flower basket.

1053
00:45:39,080 --> 00:45:40,180
Yes, we were just...

1054
00:45:40,480 --> 00:45:41,640
We were just talking about it.

1055
00:45:41,640 --> 00:45:43,180
This is a bit too extravagant.

1056
00:45:43,540 --> 00:45:45,220
- This is necessary.
- That's our gesture.

1057
00:45:45,340 --> 00:45:46,600
- Right?
- Yes.

1058
00:45:46,600 --> 00:45:47,810
Zhang Yan, take a photo for us.

1059
00:45:47,810 --> 00:45:49,260
- Come, come!
- Take a photo!

1060
00:45:49,260 --> 00:45:50,300
Come on.

1061
00:45:50,540 --> 00:45:52,540
Let's take the sign with you.

1062
00:45:52,540 --> 00:45:53,700
Yes, let's show the name!

1063
00:45:53,860 --> 00:45:55,440
You can promote our bar then.

1064
00:45:55,440 --> 00:45:57,330
Of course, everyone should post one
on your social media.

1065
00:45:57,330 --> 00:45:58,380
- Come on.
- Composition!

1066
00:45:58,380 --> 00:46:00,220
Lin Xu, move in a little
further, right there!

1067
00:46:00,220 --> 00:46:01,130
Take it from a higher angle!

1068
00:46:01,130 --> 00:46:03,140
(Banghe Bar)
Come on, three, two, one, good!

1069
00:46:03,140 --> 00:46:05,100
Let me stretch my leg. Three, two, one.

1070
00:46:05,140 --> 00:46:06,460
You look good!

1071
00:46:06,460 --> 00:46:07,820
Three, two, one, okay!

1072
00:46:07,820 --> 00:46:09,090
Three, two... Okay!

1073
00:46:09,090 --> 00:46:10,440
- So sweet.
- Let's see the photo.

1074
00:46:10,560 --> 00:46:11,740
Remember to post it on social media!

1075
00:46:11,740 --> 00:46:12,620
How's it looking?

1076
00:46:12,620 --> 00:46:14,260
- Are you satisfied?
- Perfect!

1077
00:46:14,520 --> 00:46:15,460
- Right?
- Good, good.

1078
00:46:15,460 --> 00:46:17,140
Alright, everyone, let's go inside!

1079
00:46:17,140 --> 00:46:18,260
Beautify the photos.

1080
00:46:18,260 --> 00:46:19,380
I haven't taken my photo yet!

1081
00:46:19,380 --> 00:46:20,340
Coming.

1082
00:46:20,380 --> 00:46:21,920
Where am I in the group photo?

1083
00:46:21,920 --> 00:46:23,120
Let's go inside and take more photos.

1084
00:46:23,120 --> 00:46:25,580
We've prepared special seats for you.

1085
00:46:26,180 --> 00:46:27,100
Thank you!

1086
00:46:28,700 --> 00:46:30,560
What would you like to drink or eat?

1087
00:46:30,560 --> 00:46:31,620
It's all on your tab today!

1088
00:46:31,620 --> 00:46:32,700
Yeah, it's all on me!

1089
00:46:32,700 --> 00:46:34,220
- Got it.
- Find a seat to sit.

1090
00:46:34,220 --> 00:46:36,180
Alright, go ahead and sit down.

1091
00:46:36,540 --> 00:46:37,860
Please come in.

1092
00:46:37,860 --> 00:46:39,700
Go inside.

1093
00:46:39,780 --> 00:46:40,620
Xiaolan,

1094
00:46:40,700 --> 00:46:41,540
take the order!

1095
00:46:41,740 --> 00:46:42,700
Coming.

1096
00:46:43,140 --> 00:46:44,700
Today, all the bills

1097
00:46:44,700 --> 00:46:46,060
are on me.

1098
00:46:46,060 --> 00:46:46,940
Good!

1099
00:46:46,940 --> 00:46:47,780
But

1100
00:46:48,140 --> 00:46:49,020
I hope that when you leave,

1101
00:46:49,020 --> 00:46:50,060
everyone gets a membership card.

1102
00:46:50,060 --> 00:46:50,900
Yes.

1103
00:46:51,100 --> 00:46:52,300
We have monthly,

1104
00:46:52,300 --> 00:46:53,700
quarterly and annual memberships.

1105
00:46:53,700 --> 00:46:54,700
Best to go for the annual one!

1106
00:46:56,430 --> 00:46:57,700
Let's just order a drink for now.

1107
00:46:57,700 --> 00:46:58,700
Take a look at the drink menu.

1108
00:46:58,920 --> 00:47:00,190
Let me know if you need anything.

1109
00:47:00,190 --> 00:47:02,020
- Alright, thank you.
- Thank you.

1110
00:47:07,460 --> 00:47:08,300
